CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 3, 1963, pg. 4 reads: "Guest Speaker - Former Superior Court Justice Blair F. Gunther (left), guest speaker at the "I Am an American Day" celebration, in Homewood, the past Sunday, is shown with (left to right): Mrs. Ruby Givner, beautician and civic leader; Harry Filson, superintendent of the State Office Building, Pittsburgh; Joe Durzo, 13th Ward Republican chairman, and Joe Watts, band chairman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Cadillac Eldorado convertible including clockwise from back left: Superior Court Justice Blair F. Gunther, Ruby Givner, Harry Filson, Joe Watts, and Joe Durzo, during the "I Am an American Day" celebration, Homewood
